article.headline: Saint Mary's 75, Kent St. 69
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Patrick Mills scored 26 points, including 19 in the second half as Saint Mary's of California took control and beat Kent State 75-69 Thursday night. Omar Samhan had 19 and Carlin Hughes added 14 for Saint Mary's (6-1). Brandon Parks and Chris Singletary scored 16 points apiece for Kent State (3-4), and Al Fisher had 14. Saint Mary's blew a 12-point lead and ended the first half tied 30-30. The lead see-sawed until a 3-pointer by Mills put Saint Mary's ahead for good at 52-49 with 9:19 to play. A 3-pointer by Hughes ended a 12-2 run over the next four minutes that put Saint Mary's up by double figures. Mills was 6-of-6 from the free throw line in the final 1:10 to preserve the win.
